  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Electrical Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Design, develop, and debug Electrical systems with proper shielded systems to ensure the pump, the high voltage, RF system, grounding system, and Plasma generator working properly and safely.</li>\n  <li>Select proper sensors and actuators for temperature, current, voltage, positions, gas flow, etc.</li>\n  <li>Design and develop the control connections, safety interlock systems, and PLC IO modules.</li>\n  <li>Pass the electrical system certification.</li>\n  <li>Conduct design, simulations and analyses to validate the power distribution and control panels and ensure compliance with specifications.</li>\n  <li>Ensure accurate data acquisition and feedback mechanisms for real-time control.</li>\n  <li>Selects OEM components and materials for power distribution box/control panel design</li>\n  <li>Creates and releases engineering drawings &amp; bill of materials using engineering change management process</li>\n  <li>Creates, update electrical schematics, system, and BOM list, based on requirements</li>\n  <li>Create and optimize quality check requirements for electrical, sensing, and actuator parts.</li>\n  <li>Works with multidisciplinary engineering design teams to design and modify custom and OEM system components.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in electrical engineering or related fields.</li>\n  <li>Minimum of 5 years of experience in electronic design and development in semiconductor equipment</li>\n  <li>RF generator (400kHz /13.5MHz) application experience, and deal with other RF related issues.</li>\n  <li>Hands-on experience in electrical schematic diagram, voltage circuit design for power and control.</li>\n  <li>Familiar with system level knowledge of Electrical architecture, design and certification of IO Controllers and Applications.</li>\n  <li>Knowledgeable in CAD tools like PCAD, ORCAD, ZUKEN or equivalent CAD packages for circuit design &amp; simulation.</li>\n  <li>Good understanding of different standards and compliances like – NEC, NFPA 79, UL 508A, IEC standard, SEMI Standard (Electrical) - S2, S8, S22 etc.</li>\n  <li>Ability to navigate a dynamic and at times ambiguous environment that requires frequent multitasking, prioritization, and a proactive mentality.</li>\n  <li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills and the ability to interact professionally with a diverse group of internal partners, team members, and suppliers.</li>\n  <li>Self-starting individual, with ability to take initiative and work independently.</li>\n  <li>Proven relationship management skills, including navigating the organization and influencing decisions.</li>\n</ul>",
